name: continuous dyeing, fibre, cotton | continuous dyeing, fibre, cotton | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20388/documentation

Data collected from mostly vertically integrated mills on a global level. The activity begins with untreated cotton fibres, which are first pre-treated before being dyed, and ends with cotton dyed. It includes electricity use and chemicals. It does not include the cotton fibres. ;Wastewater emissions have been modelled based on primary data and completed with default data, considering wastewater treatment.

The activity begins with loading untreated fibre. However, this is service activity. This means that the loaded fibre is not considered as an input of this process. 

The activity delivers the service of dyeing 1kg fibre. It has to be used with 1.04 kg of fibre (taking into account the fibre loss). This dataset represents a mixture of dryed and undryed fibre. This activity is for a fibre with a grammage of 236g/square meter.
category: C:Manufacturing/13:Manufacture of textiles/131:Spinning, weaving and finishing of textiles/1313:Finishing of textiles

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Eurasia, East Asia, South/Central Asia,;and Latin America
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Extrapolated from data from mostly vertically integrated mills.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data collected from mostly vertically integrated mills on a global level.

exchanges.description: Based on the Fibre Year report 2017 for the overall fibre production and assumptions on losses (17%) based on FAO World Apparel Fiber Consumption Survey 2013.
